{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id90a5a696-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6006"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6006"},"text":"§ 6006.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Policy toward a transitional Cuban Government","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Food, medicine, and medical supplies for humanitarian purposes should be made available for Cuba under the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2151"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 2151","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] and the Food for Peace Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t7/s1691"},"text":"7 U.S.C. 1691","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] if the President determines and certifies to the Committee on Foreign Affairs of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Foreign Relations of the Senate that the government in power in Cuba—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id90a5a697-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6006/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has made a public commitment to hold free and fair elections for a new government within 6 months and is proceeding to implement that decision;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id90a5a698-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6006/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has made a public commitment to respect, and is respecting, internationally recognized human rights and basic democratic freedoms; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id90a5a699-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s6006/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is not providing weapons or funds to any group, in any other country, that seeks the violent overthrow of the government of that country.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id90a5a69a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/484/dA/tXVII/s1707"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–484, div. A, title XVII, § 1707","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-23"},"text":"Oct. 23, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/2579"},"text":"106 Stat. 2579","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/tIII/s3001/b/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246, title III, § 3001(b)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (2)(V), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-06-18"},"text":"June 18, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/1820"},"text":"122 Stat. 1820","children":[],"tail":", 1821.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id90a5a69b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id90a5a69c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id90a5a69d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Foreign Assistance Act of 1961, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/195"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–195","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-09-04"},"text":"Sept. 4, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":